name: Science Center - Montgomery County Community College
directions: The Science center has only one entrance/exit on the lowest floor. By this doorway is a gender-neutral bathroom.An elevator is down the hall from this bathroom, to take you to/from the upper floors.
comment: This bathroom is intended for students, faculty and staff. That said, no-one would know if you weren't student, faculty or staff.The room is fairly wide. Door can be locked. Looks specifically designed for wheelchair users. Single occupancy.Entrance/exit doorway to the Science Center is button-operated for wheelchair users. This bathroom is frequently empty, as it is next to multi-stall female and male bathrooms.

name: NC State Student Health Services
directions: Room 2304.  2nd Floor near large classroom.  Toward back of building.
comment: Normal building hours MWThF 8-5. T 9-5.

name: Highline
comment: Also, vegan biscuits and gravy!

name: Marion McCain Arts and Social Sciences Building
directions: Second floor - lobby; two separate bathrooms on either side.
comment: Building is usually closed on weekends.

name: Rocky Mountain National Park
directions: The visitor center on the Estes Park side has accessible, family bathrooms (Beaver Meadows Visitor Center) I'm not sure about the other visitors center but many of the bathrooms in the park itself are gender neutral. In the campgrounds they could be gender specific for showers so call and ask about those before taking my word as final authority!
comment: Rocky Mountain Park is wonderful for everyone!

name: Poudre River Library - Old Town
directions: 10 yards to the right of main entrance.

name: Carson Pirie Scott
directions: Circle Centre -- the restroom is on the second floor, which is accessible by elevator. It\\'s in the back near women\\'s dresses. Not sure if the store has other bathrooms.
comment: Two genderfree bathrooms with wheelchair-accessible symbols on the door. I am not an expert on disability accessibility, but the toilet was low, there was room to manuever the space, and I think there were safety bars nearby.The store generally keeps mall hours but occasionally is open earlier or later. Normal hours are 10-9 M-Sat, 12-6 Sun.

name: Empire Espresso
directions: In the back

name: Northeastern Illinois University
street: 5500 North St. Louis Ave. Building D
directions: Enter the doors where Enrollment Services/Financial Aid/Cashier are located in the D Building. Go down one floor using the stairs or the elevator. Follow the signs for the Counseling Office. The bathrooms are on the left in this short hallway, just past the Counseling Office.
comment: Generally available 8:30 am to 5:30 pm Monday through Friday

name: Rising Tide Natural Foods COOP
directions: Inside front of building on the left, two lockable restrooms with vacant/in use indicator on the dead bolt
comment: open 7 days/seek, if all restrooms were like these there would be NO problems...Trans Friendly!

name: Fort Garry Library
directions: Go in the front entrance and it's on your right.
comment: Mon,Tue,Thurs: 10:00-20:30Wed,Fri,Sat: 10:00-17:00Sun: Closed

name: Youth Pride Inc.
directions: Bathroom is back near the kitchen. You will be asked to sign in and give your name which will be kept confidential.
comment: Drop-In center for LGBTQQ youth/young adults and their allies. Restricted to ages 13-23. Hours: M-Th 2:30-8pm, Fri 4-8pm, Sat 10am-5pm. Check our website for schedule changes and closings- www.youthprideri.org

name: Fun Spot
directions: Multiple bathrooms on multiple floors- all single stall and non-gendered. There are a couple out of the way behind the bowling rental counter.
comment: It is the largest arcade in the world! No admission, you just walk right in.

name: Uncle Nick's Greek Cuisine
directions: There are two non-gendered restrooms located downstairs below the main level of seating.
comment: Pretty good food. Monday thru FridayLunch: 11:30 thru 4:00 pmDinner: 4:00 pm thru 11:00 pmSaturday & Sunday:11:30 am thru 11:00 pm

name: Local Sprouts

name: Xtreme Bean Coffee Co
directions: On the west side of the terrace.
comment: Two single-stall, fully accessible genderless bathrooms. No Hassles, ever.

name: Flanders Gallery
comment: Only open Wednesday-Saturday

name: Smith College, Campus Center

comment: Monday to Friday 8 am to 5 pm. Closed the day of Holidays only including Presidents Day, Columbus Day, and Veteran's Day

name: Chevron gas station
directions: Requires key, just ask person at the counter and they'll get it for you. Sometimes the key is already on the counter and you can just take it.

comment: There might be parents with young children in there at times that also need the washroom.

name: Fresh Slice
directions: To the right of the cashier's counter. Does not require key.

comment: Small door that locks.  Accessible during regular business hours (9:00-4:00). Students and faculty come in and out all of the day, so be confident and you'll have no problems. Go next door to 806 and say hello to Dorothy Fillmore, LGBT subcommittee member and 100% LGBT friendly.

name: Altamont Free Library
directions: Enter library and turn left at checkout desk, walk all the way back, past stacks

name: Alterra
directions: Directly left of the cashiers, between the main room and the back room.
comment: It's a very cool foundry building turned coffee shop. Many people come in just to look around, but if you have the time and money, all of their products are made locally, in-house, and very delicious. I would suggest getting pour over coffee instead of drip, it is a few cents more, but you won't regret it!

name: Alterra
directions: If you enter through the front door, it is straight ahead past cashiers and in a hallway to the left of the seats in front of the roasting area. If you enter in the side door, you will follow the wall to your left, and turn left down the hallway.
comment: The employees are incredibly nice and allow people in the neighborhood to use the restrooms. This location is generally busy and you can go in without being noticed most of the time. The coffee is good and strong, served in many different ways (pour-over, airpot, french press) the tea is wonderful; they just created their own \"Letterbox\" brand and the food is delicious. Everything is made in that facility or at the Bayview Location.

comment: 2 gender free bathrooms with locking doors. The one facing the front door is closest. Clean but minimalist. Good old style simple diner food, big burgers and breakfasts.

directions: NW corner of building, last door on right.

Chris Alexander, MP Ajax-Pickering Constituency Office
comment: * Available to guests who are meeting with the Member of Parliament. For security reasons it is not available to the general public (no walk-ins)

name: Genetic Medicine Building, UNC Chapel Hill
directions: Enter through the Mason Farm Road side of the building. There are two single-stall bathrooms in an alcove on the left side of the foyer.
comment: You will not be able to access the building without a badge on weekdays after 6pm or on weekends.

name: Ely's Mill
directions: Either drive up Roaring Fork Road from Hwy 321 in Gatlinburg, or go the 11 miles around the Roaring Fork Motor Nature Trail.  Ely's Mill is the last stop.  They have a \"public outhouse,\" in the old style.  Literally an old-timey outhouse.  It is up near the green-roofed log barn, towards the creek.
comment: Free to the public, but sometimes a bit messy.  Also not wheel chair accessible.  No running water.  Nevertheless, it is completely devoid of gender segregation.

name: George Kenyon Building, below PC cluster
street: University of Manchester, near University Place
directions: Enter and walk sort of to the right and ahead.  There are a multitude (~3 or 4) of single-stall, dual-gendered, lock bathrooms.
comment: Open whenever the university is open.  You will need student ID to enter, but often you can just sneak in behind someone else.

name: Austin Peay Building
street: Austin Peay Building, University of Tennessee
directions: The Austin Peay, or psychology, building is located on the side of \"The Hill\" on the UTK campus towards the University Center, soon to be the Student Union.  There are single stall, dual gendered, lock bathrooms on almost every floor.  On the first floor, just enter towards Ayers Hall, and look immediately towards the right.  Other bathrooms on higher floors are in other locations.
comment: Open whenever the university is open.  Make sure to knock before opening the door, and make sure to lock while you are inside, as is common courtesy!

name: Melrose Hall
directions: Melrose is next to Hodges Library, the central library.  Enter the courtyard, (if you need a ramp, this will be on the side towards Fort Sanders), and then enter the building through the door to the right of the swing.  The bathroom is straight ahead.
comment: Open when the university is open.  Also in this building are the LGBTQ center, parts of the music program, and the remnants of the UT honors program.  It's a pretty relaxed setting.
